 Application‚Üê‚äÉ‚éïTHIS,‚ç®‚éïTHIS~‚ç®‚éïRSI/‚ç®‚éïTHIS‚çï‚çõ{(‚äÇ‚ç∫)‚â¢¬®‚çµ‚Üë¬®‚ç®‚â¢‚ç∫}‚éïNSI             ‚çù Global: Where are we being called from (outside DeltaWI)?
 :If 0=‚éïNC'#.‚çôWI' ‚ãÑ CreateRoot'#.‚çôWI' ‚ãÑ :EndIf                          ‚çù On our first call, create a root from which everything GUI grows
 GUIroot‚Üê#.‚çôWI                                                          ‚çù Global: A reference to our GUI structure root (for later use)

 :Hold '‚àÜWI#',‚çï‚éïTID ‚ãÑ top‚Üê1 ‚ãÑ :Else ‚ãÑ top‚Üê0 ‚ãÑ :EndHold                  ‚çù Is this a recursive call? ‚çù? This sequence could theoretically be interrupted by an in-thread event that might happen any time (high-priority??)
 top,‚ç®‚Üê0/‚ç®top‚àß'‚éïSend'‚â°‚ç•‚éïC‚äÉ‚äÜaction                                       ‚çù Allow a ‚éïSend to execute even while another thread is using ‚àÜWI!
 :Hold top/'‚àÜWI'('‚àÜWI#',‚çï‚éïTID)                                          ‚çù Make sure we stay single-threaded!

     ‚çù *** Pre-process the ‚àÜWI call
     nametesting‚Üê‚éïNULL‚àäaction                                           ‚çù Allow for name-parsing-only internal testing to be performed
     :If 0=‚éïNC'object' ‚ãÑ object‚Üê‚ä¢ ‚ãÑ :EndIf                              ‚çù Allow monadic use
     (objname objref action)‚Üêobject ObjectName action                   ‚çù Parse out object name to which this call applies
     :If nametesting ‚ãÑ result‚Üêobjname ‚ãÑ :Return ‚ãÑ :EndIf                ‚çù Allow for name-parsing-only internal testing to be performed
     :If resume‚Üêaction‚â°,‚äÇ,'*'                                           ‚çù Resume from within onAction handler?
         :Hold '‚àÜWI@onAction' ‚ãÑ resume‚Üê0 ‚ãÑ :Else ‚ãÑ resume‚Üê1 ‚ãÑ :EndHold  ‚çù Are we really in the middle of onAction processing that can be continued?
     :AndIf resume                                                      ‚çù Are we still only resuming (only if we're on :Hold)
